com.whirvis.jraknet.session

Interface GeminusRakNetPeer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    RakNetClientSession, RakNetServer, RakNetServerBundleExample, RakNetServerSession, RakNetSession

    public interface GeminusRakNetPeer
    This interface represents a server connection to a client, this is used mainly to keep message sending easier and consistent between the lower and higher level implementation using the session's globally unique ID.
    Author:
    Trent "Whirvis" Summerlin

      • sendMessage

        EncapsulatedPacket sendMessage(long guid,
                               Reliability reliability,
                               int channel,
                               Packet packet)
        Sends a message with the reliability on the channel to the session with the globally unique ID and returns a copy of the generated encapsulated packet that will be used when it is actually sent.
        Parameters:
        guid - the globally unique ID of the session.
        reliability - the reliability of the packet.
        channel - the channel to send the packet on.
        packet - the packet to send.
        Returns:
        the generated encapsulated packet.
        Throws:
        InvalidChannelException - if the channel is higher than the maximum.
